<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="305" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,781,151,211]" box="[151,248,186,211]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,241,186,211]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="19.[151,249,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,210,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-52@19.[230,1356,193,1933]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 10. Libelloides coccajus (Denis et Schiffermüller, 1775), 3rd instar larva (Italy: Liguria, Mt. Toraggio). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–c: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915207/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,258,1258]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">
The first accounts about the larva of this species are not informative (
<bibRefCitation author="Hagen, H. A." box="[949,1089,258,283]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" pagination="33 - 62" refId="ref16310" refString="Hagen, H. A. (1873) Die Larven von Ascalaphus. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 34, 33 - 62." type="journal article" year="1873">Hagen 1873</bibRefCitation>
) or unreliable (
<bibRefCitation author="Xambeu, P." box="[1267,1431,258,283]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" pagination="79 - 129" refId="ref17837" refString="Xambeu, P. (1903) Moeurs et metamorphoses des insectes. Annales de la Societe Linneene de Lyon, 50, 79 - 129." type="journal article" year="1903">Xambeu 1903</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacroix, J. L." box="[151,304,294,319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" pagination="65 - 100" refId="ref16539" refString="Lacroix, J. L. (1923) Faune des Planipennes de France. Ascalaphidae. Bulletin de la Societe d'Etude des Sciences Naturelles d'Elbeuf, 41, 65 - 100." type="journal article" year="1923">Lacroix 1923</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<bibRefCitation author="Eglin, W." box="[395,538,294,319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" pagination="243 - 358" refId="ref16129" refString="Eglin, W. (1940) Die Neuropteren der Umgebung von Basel. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 47, 243 - 358." type="journal article" year="1940">Eglin (1940)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the hatching behaviour of the first instar larvae. Surprisingly the first exhaustive description of the larva of this species, one of the more common and widespread European ascalaphids, was relatively recently realized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rousset, A." box="[547,722,366,391]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" pagination="164 - 178" refId="ref17391" refString="Rousset, A. (1973) Morphologie externe et caracteres distinctifs des larves de trois especes d'Ascalaphes [Nevropteres, Planipennes]. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 78, 164 - 178." type="journal article" year="1973">Rousset (1973)</bibRefCitation>
. Finally, a photo of a larva appears in U. Aspöck &amp; H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Aspock, U. &amp; Aspock, H." pageId="18" pageNumber="305" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref15574" refString="Aspock, U. &amp; Aspock, H. (1999) Kamelhalse, Schlammfliegen, Ameisenlowen. Wer sind sie? (Insecta: Neuropterida: Raphidioptera, Megaloptera, Neuroptera). Stapfia, 60, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1999">Aspöck (1999)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
