<collectingCountry box="[1020,1099,1126,1149]" name="France" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1164,1125,1150]" name="Italy" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1177,1314,1125,1150]" name="Switzerland" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1432,1125,1150]" name="Germany" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,334,1161,1186]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="305" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,258,1258]" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1197,1222]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis et Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[470,598,1198,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coccajus">
<emphasis box="[470,598,1198,1221]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="305">L. coccajus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks noteworthy diagnostic characters, being mostly recognizable due to the dark brown hue of the body and the dilated posterior margins of the head capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
